At least 16 cadres in Hubei were disciplined during the epidemic prevention and control, the highest number of cadres punished in the public notification

This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Du Maolin, southern weekend reporter

By Jiang Zhiyu, southern weekend staff writer

Editor in chief | Qian Haoping

On January 27,2020, on the third day of the first lunar month, deputy scientific officer Chen Liang, deputy secretary of the Party Committee of Dajipu town in Daye, Hubei Province (county level) , was somewhat glum because of his ineffective work in the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, and received a warning from the party.

The specific reason is that the village under the jurisdiction of the big JI shop "epidemic prevention and control measures are virtually non-existent" , Chen Liang as the village leader, with the village party branch secretary of the village, Shi Jiaoguo, big JI shop town agricultural director Fu Yuhong was punished.

In the prevention and control of this epidemic, more than three cadres have been disciplined since the "closure" of Wuhan. As of January 29, according to the statistics of the southern weekend reporter, at least 33 cadres across the country have been disciplined, some have been warned and some have been dismissed from their posts, individual cases were also filed for review by the Commission for Discipline Inspection.

Among them, there are not only office-level cadres, but also department-level cadres. More of them are grass-roots cadres who are in the front line.

1
The Disciplinary Commission Killed The "return of duty" 

1

###The Disciplinary Commission Killed The "return of duty" 

Chen Liang is the punishment of the grass-roots cadres, he is the first day of the first month by the Commission for Discipline Inspection found that "weak prevention and control. ".

At about 3:00 pm that day, the Daye Commission of discipline inspection went to the village of Ba Liu to supervise the prevention and control of the epidemic. This is the largest administrative village of Huangshi (Daye is part of Huangshi) , with a population of more than 7,000 and 24 natural villages.

At this time, Huangshi has been confirmed cases of 31 cases, one death, the previous day (January 24) that is the 30th of the 12th month "closed city. ".

But the epidemic did not stop the "colorful" entertainment in the village of Balu in southeastern Hubei Province. The Commission for Discipline Inspection found that many villagers were playing cards in the street snack bars, chess and card rooms and other four places. Most of them did not even wear masks.

Disciplinary Commission staff will gather the villagers to persuade away, the situation to the town Party Committee, the government made feedback. Chen Liang recalled to southern weekend reporters that he was not at a meeting in Daye when the disciplinary commission went to supervise. After learning the situation, he quickly gave instructions to the village General Party secretary to let him each family to do the work. Shi Jiaoguo, who has been removed from his post as party chief, told southern weekend that he and several village officials rushed to the scene immediately and told villagers to pay attention to prevention and control and not to gather. But the villagers think the epidemic prevention and control has nothing to do with them, "also said some unpleasant words. ".

But a few hours later, at 9 pm that night, the Daye Disciplinary Commission killed again. Secret visit found that there are still villagers gathered "colored" playing cards.

The next day, Chen Liang was called in for questioning by the disciplinary commission. "It was so sudden, " Chen Liang said. "I called an emergency meeting on the 23rd and began to deploy all kinds of work. This happened on the 25th. " Chen Liang said that there were only eight village cadres in a village the size of Balu, and the pressure on prevention and control was relatively high, "The village gathers the crowd we all promptly dissuades, but is like the water hyacinth, this pressed that to rise. ".

Soon after, the disciplinary action was taken against all three of them, including Chen Liang. Chen Liang felt that the effect of accountability "is still very obvious, " villagers now more understanding and cooperation epidemic prevention work, generally do not go out, 95% of people will wear masks, "as of now, there is no confirmed or suspected cases of Balu village.

According to Chen Liang, on the fourth day of the first lunar month, the Hubei provincial inspection team went to check on their work "very high evaluation. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(Du Maolin / photo by Southern Weekend Reporter)

2
To release false information

2

###To release false information

Southern weekend reporters noted that in addition to Chen Liang and three other people, at least 13 other cadres in Hubei were also held accountable during the epidemic prevention and control, which is currently the province with the largest number of cadres publicly notified and punished, among them, Xiang Jianghong, deputy director of the village committee of Baishulin Village, Huaqiao Town, Wuxue City, Huanggang, was punished for publishing false information.

On January 21, Huanggang announced 12 confirmed cases. The next day, a report of the outbreak circulated in Huaqiao Town; "Huaqiao has now had a case of COVID-19 pneumonia, and has been sent to Wuhan, the People's Hospital of Wuxue City did not receive" , was posted by Xiang Jianghong. According to the Wuxue Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision, the news was based on hearsay by Xiang Jianghong, who sent the content to her 81-person wechat group, which caused widespread dissemination.

After the investigation was verified, the Wuxue Commission for Discipline Inspection and Supervision of Xiang Jianghong Party discipline record, and handed over to the police station, on the night of January 23, Xiang Jianghong was removed from party posts.

Southern weekend reporters noted that 33 people were disciplined for not performing their duties, but there were also cadres who deliberately withheld information, including Zhang Xiayou, secretary of the Party branch of Shaao village in Wenling, Zhejiang.

In public reports, Zhejiang Province has punished four cadres. Zhang Xiayou was dismissed from his job after he was accused of severely violating the rules of epidemic prevention and control by concealing the fact that his son and three other relatives had returned home from Wuhan.

3
Timely adjustment of incompetent cadres

3

###Timely adjustment of incompetent cadres

Of the 33 cadres who were disciplined, Wang Zengtian was the most senior. Wang Zengtian, a 49-year-old office-level cadre who was appointed as the second-level inspector of the Tianjin Municipal Health Commission, was detained by the Party for two years and removed from his post for "serious dereliction of duty and causing serious adverse effects" in the prevention and control work.

Compared with the confirmed cases in Beijing, Shanghai and Chongqing, the number of confirmed cases in Tianjin is relatively small. As of 9:00 on January 29,27 cases of pneumonia with COVID-19 infection had been found in Tianjin, with no critical or fatal cases.

On the day before Wang Zengtian was punished, the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China issued the notice on strengthening the leadership of the Party and providing strong political guarantee for winning the War of resistance against and control of epidemic diseases, even those who engage in fraud or dereliction of duty should be severely held accountable.

After the announcement, a commentary on the website of the Central Commission for Discipline Inspection, the State Supervision and Administration Commission, called on local commissions of discipline to provide strong discipline to win the battle for epidemic prevention and control. A few days ago, the Central Organization Department also issued a notice, stressing that attention should be paid to the inspection and identification of leading groups and cadres in the front line of epidemic prevention and control, and timely adjustment of cadres who are not competent for their current posts and are unable to effectively carry out their duties.
